# Core Workflow

Important rules:
- Follow project-specific audio behavior requirements first.
- Keep backward compatibility for snapshots when changing playback modes.
- Keep snapshot coding system untouchible, don't change the pricipe of  hashing. You can add but not re-build
- Before push: см. `git-push-commit-label.mdc` (SHA в UI — из Vite при build, не хардкод под HEAD коммита).
- UI Safety Rule (strict): any UI/UX/layout/visual behavior changes in Cursor project files are forbidden by default unless the user explicitly approves that exact UI change in the current chat. If approval is missing, do not modify UI at all.
- UI Geometry Lock (strict): even "minor" visual tweaks are forbidden without explicit user approval. Prohibited without approval: width/height/min/max constraints, padding/margin/gap, font-size/line-height, whitespace/wrapping behavior, border/radius/shadow changes that alter perceived element size, and any style edits that can shift or resize UI blocks.

Related:
- `git-push-commit-label.mdc`
